<subSubSection lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="114" pageId="25" pageNumber="112" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[801,1453,1599,1946]" lastBlockId="27.[113,765,279,498]" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="114" pageId="25" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis box="[839,921,1600,1623]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="112">Notes. –</emphasis>
The only collection of this species in Ventenat’s herbarium is mixed: a Ventenat collection from Cels’s garden and fragments of possible isotypes (G [G00341643 specimen on the right]) of 
<taxonomicName authority="Michx." authorityName="Michx." box="[972,1264,1696,1720]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Polygonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="25" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parvifolia">
<emphasis box="[972,1183,1696,1720]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="112">Polygonella parvifolia</emphasis>
Michx.
</taxonomicName>
, a name published one year later (
<bibRefCitation author="Michaux, A." box="[961,1135,1728,1752]" journalOrPublisher="Paris" pageId="25" pageNumber="112" refId="ref26623" refString="Michaux, A. (1803). Flora Boreali-Americana. 2 vol. Paris." title="Flora Boreali-Americana. 2 vol." type="book" year="1803">Michaux, 1803</bibRefCitation>
) (with a duplicate in P-JU n° 4290 [P00681748]). The latter name is probably based on the same original material as mentioned on the sheet by Vernon M. Bates (
<figureCitation box="[871,943,1825,1849]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="28.[136,163,1928,1947]" captionTargetBox="[302,1307,276,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-17@28.[302,1307,276,1899]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Fig. 11. – Mixed gathering on the single sheet of Polygonum polygamum Vent. at G [see under n° 63 for further explanations]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5722258" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5722258/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="112">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) but we failed to find convincing type material in P-MICH due to the complicated taxonomy of the mixed collections and leave this to a specialist of this genus. 
<bibRefCitation author="Horton, J. H." journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="25" pageNumber="112" pagination="177 - 203" part="15" refId="ref25674" refString="Horton, J. H. (1963). A taxonomic revision of Polygonella (Polygonaceae). Brittonia 15: 177 - 203." title="A taxonomic revision of Polygonella (Polygonaceae)" type="journal article" year="1963">Horton (1963: 198)</bibRefCitation>
designated tab. 65 of 
<emphasis box="[1077,1198,1922,1945]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="112">Descriptions</emphasis>
in 1802 as the 
<typeStatus box="[1357,1452,1922,1946]" pageId="25" pageNumber="112">lectotype</typeStatus>
for the name 
<taxonomicName box="[254,479,279,303]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Polygonum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="27" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="polygamum">
<emphasis box="[254,479,279,303]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="114">Polygonum polygamum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but as original material has been found, our lectotypification supersedes the previous one. We designate Ventenat’s collection as the 
<typeStatus box="[531,623,344,368]" pageId="27" pageNumber="114">lectotype</typeStatus>
(specimen on the left of the sheet marked with an asterix). Recent molecular phylogenetic data show that 
<taxonomicName authority="Michx." authorityName="Michx." box="[410,600,409,433]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Polygonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="27" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[410,520,409,433]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="114">Polygonella</emphasis>
Michx.
</taxonomicName>
is embedded in 
<taxonomicName box="[113,221,441,465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Polygonum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="27" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[113,221,441,465]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="114">Polygonum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. and 
<taxonomicName box="[301,411,441,465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Polygonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="27" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[301,411,441,465]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="114">Polygonella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently recognised at the subsectional level within 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schuster et al., 2011)" baseAuthorityName="Schuster" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[335,698,473,498]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Polygonum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="27" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[335,443,473,497]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="114">Polygonum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schuster, T. M. &amp; J. L. Reveal &amp; K. A. Kron" box="[458,690,473,498]" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="27" pageNumber="114" pagination="1653 - 1666" part="60" refId="ref27241" refString="Schuster, T. M., J. L. Reveal &amp; K. A. Kron (2011). Phylogeny of Polygoneae (Polygonaceae: Polygonoideae). Taxon 60: 1653 - 1666." title="Phylogeny of Polygoneae (Polygonaceae: Polygonoideae)" type="journal article" year="2011">Schuster et al., 2011</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
